## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="b1fcd-286"><xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataReader.GetOrdinal%2A> realiza una búsqueda de mayúsculas y minúsculas en primer lugar.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1fcd-286"><xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataReader.GetOrdinal%2A> performs a case-sensitive lookup first.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b1fcd-287">Si se produce un error, se realiza una segunda búsqueda entre mayúsculas y minúsculas.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1fcd-287">If it fails, a second case-insensitive search is made.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b1fcd-288">El método produce una `IndexOutOfRange` excepción si no se encuentra el ordinal de columna basado en cero.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1fcd-288">The method throws an `IndexOutOfRange` exception if the zero-based column ordinal is not found.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="b1fcd-289"><xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataReader.GetOrdinal%2A> distingue kana y ancho de minúsculas.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1fcd-289"><xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataReader.GetOrdinal%2A> is kana-width insensitive.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="b1fcd-290">Dado que las búsquedas basadas en ordinales son más eficaces que las búsquedas con nombre, resulta poco útil llamar a <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataReader.GetOrdinal%2A> dentro de un bucle.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1fcd-290">Because ordinal-based lookups are more efficient than named lookups, it is inefficient to call <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataReader.GetOrdinal%2A> within a loop.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b1fcd-291">En su lugar, llame a <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataReader.GetOrdinal%2A> una vez y a continuación, asigne los resultados a una variable entera para usar en el bucle.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1fcd-291">Instead, call <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataReader.GetOrdinal%2A> once and then assign the results to an integer variable for use within the loop.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="b1fcd-292">En el siguiente ejemplo se muestra cómo se utiliza el método <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataReader.GetOrdinal%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b1fcd-292">The following example demonstrates how to use the <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataReader.GetOrdinal%2A> method.</span></span>  
  
```vb  
Public Sub ReadOracleData(ByVal connectionString As String)  
  
    Dim queryString As String = "SELECT OrderID, CustomerID FROM Orders"  
    Dim connection As New OracleConnection(connectionString)  
    Dim command As New OracleCommand(queryString, connectionString)  
  
    connection.Open()  
  
    Dim reader As OracleDataReader = command.ExecuteReader()  
  
    Dim custIdCol As Integer = reader.GetOrdinal("CustomerID")  
  
    Do While reader.Read()  
        Console.WriteLine("CustomerID = {0}", reader.GetString(custIdCol))  
    Loop  
  
    reader.Close()  
    connection.Close()  
End Sub  
```  
  
```csharp  
public void ReadOracleData(string connectionString)  
{  
    string queryString = "SELECT OrderID, CustomerID FROM Orders";  
    OracleConnection connection = new OracleConnection(connectionString);  
    OracleCommand command = new OracleCommand(queryString,connection);  
  
    connection.Open();  
    OracleDataReader reader = command.ExecuteReader();  
  
    int custIdCol = reader.GetOrdinal("CustomerID");  
  
    while (reader.Read())  
        Console.WriteLine("CustomerID = {0}", reader.GetString(custIdCol));  
  
    reader.Close();  
    connection.Close();  
}  
```
